        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add Codex pace headroom hint",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Show `Try 1.5x!` when Codex usage is on pace to finish with more than 15% reserve and the projected headroom supports at least 1.5x usage.\n- Add an Advanced setting for historical pace lookback, defaulting to 3 complete Codex weeks and allowing 2-8 weeks for local tuning/testing.\n- Improve Ollama's browser-cookie error when macOS blocks access, so users see Full Disk Access guidance instead of a misleading \"no session cookie\" message.\n\n## Why\n\nCodexBar already computes session/weekly pace and historical Codex pace, but the previous copy only said usage was \"in reserve\", which is easy to miss and not actionable. The new hint translates meaningful reserve into a simple user action: try using Codex faster when the current/history-adjusted pace suggests the quota will still last until reset.\n\nThe historical lookback was temporarily lowered to 2 weeks for testing. This PR turns that into a real preference instead of hard-coding the test value, keeping the production default at 3 weeks while letting Advanced users tune the threshold.\n\nOllama cookie import can fail before CodexBar can inspect any session cookie if macOS denies access to the browser cookie database, especially Safari's protected cookie store. That previously collapsed into \"No Ollama session cookie found\", which reads like an Ollama login problem. This PR preserves the existing import order and cookie recognition, but surfaces the access-denied hint so the user knows to grant Full Disk Access.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- `UsagePace.speedMultiplierToReset` estimates safe usage multiplier as `expectedUsedPercent / actualUsedPercent`.\n- UI/CLI only show `Try 1.5x!` when reserve is greater than 15% and the multiplier is at least 1.5.\n- `historicalPaceMinimumWeeks` is stored in defaults, clamped to `2...8`, observed for menu refresh, and passed into `CodexHistoricalPaceEvaluator`.\n- Advanced settings exposes the lookback as a stepper.\n- Ollama automatic cookie import now collects `BrowserCookieError.accessDeniedHint` values and reports them as a typed browser-access error when no session can be imported.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter SettingsStoreCoverageTests`\n- `swift test --filter HistoricalUsagePaceTests`\n- `swift test --filter OllamaUsageFetcherTests`\n- `swift test --filter OllamaUsageParserTests`\n- `CODEXBAR_SIGNING=adhoc ./Scripts/package_app.sh debug`\n- Launched `/Users/clawd/Projects/CodexBar/CodexBar.app` locally.\n\n## Local Testing Note\n\nFor local verification only, I set:\n\n```sh\ndefaults write com.steipete.codexbar.debug historicalPaceMinimumWeeks -int 2\ndefaults write com.steipete.codexbar.debug historicalTrackingEnabled -bool true\n```\n\nThose defaults are not part of the committed changes.",
